<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="676" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[113,1089,219,1587]" pageId="19" pageNumber="676">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,365,1307,1331]" pageId="19" pageNumber="676">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Bílý &amp; Brûlé, 2013" authorityName="Bílý &amp; Brûlé" authorityYear="2013" box="[373,552,1309,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="676" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[373,552,1309,1332]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="676">Agrilaxia glabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[561,645,1308,1331]" pageId="19" pageNumber="676" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gory" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[812,933,1309,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="676" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bivittata">
<emphasis box="[812,933,1309,1332]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="676">A. bivittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group resembling by its body-shape and rather dark colouration 
<taxonomicName authority="Bílý &amp; Brûlé, 2013" authorityName="Bílý &amp; Brûlé" authorityYear="2013" box="[725,835,1340,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="676" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[725,741,1341,1364]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="676">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[754,835,1341,1364]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="676">elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[842,924,1340,1363]" pageId="19" pageNumber="676" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": BELLAMY (2008:" authorityYear="1501" box="[974,1081,1341,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="676" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claudei">
<emphasis box="[974,1081,1341,1364]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="676">A. claudei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs strongly from both by the glabrous and lustrous elytra without any trace of longitudinal carinae, poorly developed posthumeral carina, strongly reduced elytral epipleura, almost regularly convex pronotum without “agriloid” carinae, deep pronotal depressions and by the emarginate anterior margin of clypeus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
